member.name: T:Syncfusion.HtmlConverter.HtmlToPdfConverter
member.summary: Class which allows converting HTML to PDF.

example.code: 'Initialize HtmlToPdfConverter class with IE rendering Engine. Dim htmlConverter As New HtmlToPdfConverter() 'Converting HTML to PDF Dim pdfDocument As PdfDocument = htmlConverter.Convert("http://www.google.com") 'Saving and closing PDF document pdfDocument.Save("Output.pdf") pdfDocument.Close(True)

member.name: M:Syncfusion.HtmlConverter.HtmlToPdfConverter.Convert(System.String)
member.summary: Converts URL to PdfDocument

example.code: 'Initialize HtmlToPdfConverter class with IE rendering Engine. Dim htmlConverter As New HtmlToPdfConverter(RenderEngine.IE) 'Setting properties for IE conversion. Dim ieSettings As New IEConverterSettings() ieSettings.AdditionalDelay = 1000 'Convert HTML to PDF. Dim pdfDocument As PdfDocument = htmlConverter.Convert("http://www.google.com") 'Saving and closing PDF document pdfDocument.Save("Output.pdf") pdfDocument.Close(True)

member.name: M:Syncfusion.HtmlConverter.HtmlToPdfConverter.Convert(System.String,Syncfusion.Pdf.Graphics.PdfLayoutResult@)
member.summary: Converts URL to PdfDocument

example.code: 'Initialize HtmlToPdfConverter class with IE rendering Engine. Dim htmlConverter As New HtmlToPdfConverter(RenderEngine.IE) 'Setting properties for IE conversion. Dim ieSettings As New IEConverterSettings() ieSettings.AdditionalDelay = 1000 'Get the layout result after conversion PdfLayoutResult layoutResult = null 'Convert HTML to PDF. Dim pdfDocument As PdfDocument = htmlConverter.Convert("http://www.google.com", out layoutResult) 'Saving and closing PDF document pdfDocument.Save("Output.pdf") pdfDocument.Close(True)

member.name: M:Syncfusion.HtmlConverter.Natives.KernelApi.WaitForSingleObject(System.IntPtr,System.UInt32)
member.summary: Waits until the specified object is in the signaled state or the time-out interval elapses.
member.param: A handle to the object. If this handle is closed while the wait is still pending, the function's behavior is undefined.

The time-out interval, in milliseconds. If a nonzero value is specified, the function waits until the object is signaled or the interval elapses. If dwMilliseconds is zero, the function does not enter a wait state if the object is not signaled; it always returns immediately. If dwMilliseconds is INFINITE, the function will return only when the object is signaled
member.returns: If the function succeeds, the return value indicates the event that caused the function to return.
